<p><iframe src="/boogey-man23-author-page/html/6f0ad53ad8d15c1222fecbe0221ba0e3a753e601-731321881426962739" allowtransparency="true" frameborder="0" class="html-block-iframe"></iframe></p>
<p>SCP voice-acting by me. Audio edited by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/chrisakapiefish" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1578588); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1578588&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610080657" alt="ChrisAKAPiefish" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1578588)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/chrisakapiefish" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1578588); return false;">ChrisAKAPiefish</a></span>.</p>
<p>&#8230;</p>
<hr />
<blockquote>
<p>SCP Idea: The Reverse-Chicken. So instead of a chicken that lays eggs, it's an egg that hatches into&#8230; oh.. never mind.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<blockquote>
<p>There once was a Redd fire truck,<br />
That came to life by some luck,<br />
SCP-4601,<br />
He went on the run,<br />
And the Foundation said &quot;Oh f- uhh, that sucks.&quot;</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<blockquote>
<p><em>Dear B_Man,</em></p>
<p><em>In certain articles, I see reality benders being referred to as &quot;bixbies&quot;. Can you explain this nickname?</em></p>
</blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p>Bill Bixby was an actor, perhaps best known for his role playing Dr. David Banner on the television series <em>The Incredible Hulk</em>.</p>
<p>On that show, the Dr. Banner character would, in times of anger or stress, transform into the Hulk; a powerful green creature.</p>
<p>In a way, a Type Green Reality Bender might also be categorized as a powerful green creature; just like the Incredible Hulk, who was actually Dr. Banner, who was played by Bill Bixby.</p>
<p>Hence the reason why Reality Benders / Type Greens are called by the vernacular &quot;Bixbies&quot;.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<p>&#8230;</p>
